Here is the fixed function:

```java
private void writeBits(final DataOutput header, final BitSet bits, final int length) throws IOException {
    int cache = 0;
    int shift = 7; // Start with the highest bit position in a byte
    for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) {
        // Set the correct bit in the cache based on the BitSet value
        if (bits.get(i)) {
            cache |= (1 << shift);
        }
        --shift; // Move to the next bit position

        // When we have filled a byte, write it out
        if (shift < 0) {
            header.write(cache); // Write the cached byte
            shift = 7; // Reset shift to the last bit position
            cache = 0; // Reset cache for the next byte
        }
    }

    // If there are any remaining bits in the cache, we need to write them out
    if (shift < 7) { // This means some bits were set in the last byte
        header.write(cache); // Write the remaining bits
    }
}
```

